This paper is about a neural network based task-oriented dialogue system that uses deep reinforcement learning for end-to-end optimization. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning and reinforcement learning, which are also associated with the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also involves human-computer interaction, which is associated with the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulations and experiments, which are associated with the cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-category.
